    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-06-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="183"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Clay</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-06-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 12, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>S<hi rend="smallcaps">ir</hi>: Your despatch of May 19 (No. 4) has been submitted
                    to the President. You will have learned from a previous communication of mine
                    the sentiments which his government has thought proper to express concerning the
                    condition of affairs in Poland.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cassius</hi> M. <hi rend="smallcaps">Clay</hi>, <hi
                            rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
